2) write about history of python:
     *Python is a popular high-level programming language created by Guido van Rossum. He started developing Python in the late 1980s at CWI (Centrum Wiskunde & Informatica) in the Netherlands. Python was officially released in 1991.

The name “Python” was inspired by the British comedy television show Monty Python's Flying Circus. Guido van Rossum selected this name because it was short, unique, and interesting.
   
